    { name: 'Melanocortin 4 receptor', type: 'MedicalEntity', sameAs: ['https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melanocortin_4_receptor'] },
  ]}
>
  <KeyTakeaways
    items={[
      'Bremelanotide (PT-141, brand name Vyleesi) is an FDA-approved melanocortin agonist for hypoactive sexual desire disorder in premenopausal women — the first on-demand treatment for the condition.',
      'It works in the brain, activating MC4R circuits that drive sexual desire, rather than improving blood flow like Viagra and other PDE5 inhibitors.',
      'It descends from the tanning peptide Melanotan II — chemists turned its arousal side effect into a drug.',
      'The approved product is a 1.75 mg subcutaneous autoinjector; the “PT-141” sold online as vials or nasal sprays is unapproved and of unknown purity.',
